  id: Radius_R
  partName: Radius Right
  descriptionChunks:
  - The right radius is one of the primary bones of the canine forearm and is positioned
    along the medial side of the forelimb. It extends from the elbow to the carpal
    joint and plays a major role in weight-bearing and locomotion.
  - The radius articulates with the humerus proximally and the carpal bones distally,
    enabling smooth movement of the forelimb during activity. It also provides attachment
    points for muscles controlling wrist and paw motion.
